cases #13CM577, #14CF3, #14CF67 called at 2:16pm. 
Defendant Georgette Amber Swenson in court with Attorney Yelena Zarwell.  ADA Brookellen Teuber appears for the State of Wisconsin.
The Court notes that it received a proposed stipulation to continue the cases, however it is not inclined to grant a continuance because the Court has learned of a further SCRAM-monitoring program notification.
Attorney Zarwell reports that Ms. Swenson is now compliant with the SCRAM program-- there was a download yesterday with good results, and Ms. Swenson has made a payment and will continue making payments as best as she is able; there was a problem with Ms. Swenson's telephone connection, but the telephone is hooked up now. 
The Court directs the Sheriff's Deputy who is present to take Ms. Swenson to the Jail for drug and alcohol testing; the Court will await these test results to determine how to proceed.  
recess 2:18pm. reconvene 3:04pm.
ADA Teuber summarizes that the JCSO Deputies report that Ms. Swenson tested positive for THC and for the presence of morphine.  Additionally the deputies report that Ms. Swenson made statements, during the testing, that she used THC two months ago and that she had taken a friend's prescription a couple of days ago, and that's why she tests positive for morphine today.  

The Court orders Ms. Swenson detained now on a $2,500 cash bond, that applies to all three files, with conditions: 
--no possession or consumption of alcohol
--no possession or ingestion of controlled substances without a valid prescription
--no possession of drug paraphernalia without a valid prescription
--no presence in bars, taverns, liquor stores
--no direct or indirect contact with Andrew Regener (dob 8/30/1974) or with Thomas Ruzicka 
--to take all prescription medications only as prescribed
--to report and comply with SCRAM alcohol monitoring program as administered by Wisconsin Community Services.  Defendant to comply with all SCRAM Program conditions of participation including payment of program costs and fees.  To report to Room 230 of the Jefferson County Courthouse at 1:30pm on the first Thursday immediately after Ms. Swenson's release from incarceration
--if released, to report to the Jefferson County Jail on the first and third Friday of each month between the hours of 9:00am to 11:00am, or 2:00pm to 4:00pm for alcohol and drug testing.  The Jail should keep track of the costs for this testing, because the Court may require reimbursement of this cost. 

The Court denies Ms. Swenson's requests for consideration to lower the cash bail amount.
recess 3:17pm.
